  <h2>Add TellMyPolitician To Your Site</h2>
</div>
<div class="contentcontainer">

  <p>
    The TellMyPolitician Button allows users to click a button on your site to share content with their politicians, much like they would click a Digg, Reddit, or StumbleUpon button to share your content across the web. We understand that people are most likely to contact their politicians when they read or watch the news. That is why we want to help users act on those urges to get their voices heard. Not only will users contact their politician from your site&#8212;they will be sharing your original content with them.
  </p>
  <p>
    Add TellMyPolitician to your site in one of the following ways:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#JSButton">Javascript Button</a></li>
    <li><a href="#wordpress">Wordpress Plugin</a></li>
    <li><a href="#blogger">Blogger Integration</a></li>
    <li><a href="#more">More To Come...</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2><a name="JSButton">Javascript Button</a></h2>
  <p>
    To add TellMyPolitician to your site simply copy and paste the code snippet below between the &lt;body&gt; and &lt;/body&gt; tags in your site. You can also add the code to your template files to easily add the button to all pages on your site. You could even include it with other social bookmarking tools your site already uses. Feel free to customize this code in any way necessary to make it work within your site.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Button Only</h3>
<p><strong>Example</strong>:
    <script type="text/javascript">
		function tmp_click() {
		var url = escape(location.href);
		var title = escape(document.title);
		var tlocation = 'http://tellmypolitician.com/search?u=' + url + '&title=' + title;
		document.location=tlocation;
		return false;
		}
		</script>
		<a href="http://tellmypolitician.com/search?" title="Contact Your Representatives" onclick="return tmp_click()" target="_blank"><img src="http://tellmypolitician.com/images/design/tmp_publisher_button.png" hspace="5"></a>
</p>
