<h2><a name="wordpress">Wordpress Plugin</a></h2>
<p>
  This plugin adds a footer link to share the current post or page with your politician using TellMyPolitician.com. While the plugin is activated, a link will appear after the content of the post with the text &quot;TellMyPolitician&quot; or the TellMyPolitician icon or both. Clicking this link will bring the user to the TellMyPolitician site. Once at TellMyPolitician, the user will be directed to input their address to find their politician. Clicking on a politician's email will allow users to copy and paste your site link into the email field to tell the politician about the article on your site.
</p>
<b>Installation:</b><br/>
<ol>
  <li>Add the folder called tellmypolitician-plugin (without the quotes) to your '/wp-content/plugins/' directory.</li>
  <li>Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress.</li>
  <li>Go to 'Settings-> TellMyPolitician' in your admin interface to select your options.</li>
</ol>
<b>CSS:</b><br/>
<p>
  The CSS for this plugin is found in the included tellmypolitician.css file. This file may be edited to change the style of the link.
</P>
<p>
  Download the <a href="http://tellmypolitician.com/files/tellmypolitician-plugin.zip">TellMyPolitician Wordpress Plugin</a>.
